    <bootstrap thing="rGlide">
      <assignval field="CustDesc" value="An entombed can glide through ice, snow, or slush as easily as a fish swims through water.  Its burrowing leaves behind no tunnel or hole, and its passage does not create any ripples or other signs of its presence.{BR}An entombed often fights from the cover of an ice sheet or snow field in much the same way that an incorporeal creature can use a wall or floor for cover.  An entombed attacking a creature outside the ice or snow in which it is hiding gains the benefit of cover."/>
