  <thing id="fAltiAdapt" name="Altitude Adaptation" description="Your body adapts quickly to changes in altitude, preventing you from suffering as much from altitude sickness.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Base Fortitude save bonus +2.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You gain a +4 bonus on all Fortitude saving throws to avoid the effects of altitude. Additionally, when you determine what effect the altitude has on you, you apply the effect for the next lower category of altitude than the category you are actually in. After you spend a week at a specific altitude, you become acclimated to that altitude and all lower altitudes, and no longer have to make Fortitude saving throws for each 6-hour period to avoid altitude sickness. If you travel to a lower altitude and remain there for a week, you lose your acclimation to the higher altitude and must reacclimatize, although you always retain the other benefits granted by this feat.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: This feat grants a +2 bonus on all Survival checks made in high altitude (above 5,000 feet) areas.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="+4 bonus vs altitude effects, reduced effect if fail, quickly acclimate." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Base Fortitude save +2 required."><![CDATA[child[vFort].field[vBase].value >= 2]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fArcticPri" name="Arctic Priest" description="You can swap out prepared spells to cast spells to aid in exploring and surviving in frostfell areas.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Access to Cold or Winter cleric domain.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You can channel stored spell energy into spells that aid in exploring and surviving in the frostfell, even if you did not prepare these spells ahead of time. You can &#147;lose&#148; any prepared spell that is not a domain spell in order to cast any of the spells that appear on the list below, as long as the spell to be cast is of an equal or lower level to the one you lose.\n\nSpells you can spontaneously cast when using this feat include: {i}control weather{/i}, {i}create food and water{/i}, {i}endure elements{/i}, {i}heroes&#146; feast{/i}, {i}hibernate{/i}, {i}protection from energy{/i}, and {i}resist energy{/i}.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="Spontaneously convert cleric spells into a small list useful in survival." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fBeckonFro" name="Beckon the Frozen" description="Creatures you summon are infused with cold energy and have the cold subtype.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Augment Summoning, Spell Focus (conjuration).\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: When you summon a creature or creatures using any summon spell, you can opt to summon a version of the creature from an extraplanar frostfell. If you do so, the summoned creature gains the cold subtype, and its natural attacks deal an additional 1d6 points of cold damage.\n\nCreatures with the fire subtype can never be enhanced with the cold subtype in this manner.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="May summon frostfell versions of creatures." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Spell Focus (conjuration) required."><![CDATA[child[ssConjur].tagis[Broadcast.SpellFocus] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Augment Summoning required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fAugSumm] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fChosIbori" name="Chosen of Iborighu" description="Your skin has a noticeable blue tint and your left eye is pale blue (your right eye is some other color); these features identify you as an ally to the church of Iborighu and grant you supernatural qualities.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Patron deity must be Iborighu.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Your left eye radiates faint evocation magic if it is viewed with a {i}detect magic{/i} spell, and faint evil if viewed with a {i}detect evil{/i} spell.\n\nCleric is now a favored class for you; the cleric class does not count when determining whether you take an experience point penalty for multiclassing.\n\nOnce per day, you can cause one creature within 30 feet that meets your gaze to become overwhelmed with a wave of supernatural cold. The target can resist the effects of this attack with a successful Fortitude save (DC 10 + 1/2 your character level + your Charisma modifier), otherwise it causes cold damage equal to your Charisma modifier + 3 (minimum 1 point of damage) and causes the victim to become fatigued. If you use this attack against someone who is fatigued, they instead become exhausted. Using this supernatural ability is a standard action that does not provoke attacks of opportunity.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: If you ever lose favor with Iborighu, or change your patron deity to another deity, you lose all benefits of this feat but your unusual skin color and eye color remain. You do not gain a replacement feat. If you later return to Iborighu&#146;s faithful and receive an {i}atonement{/i} spell, you regain the benefits of the feat.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="Cleric is favored class. 1/day, gaze for X cold dam &amp; fatigue (DCYY Fort neg)." uniqueness="useronce">
    <fieldval field="hTotal" value="1"/>
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostAt" priority="10000"><![CDATA[var DC as number
DC = 10 + hero.child[aCHA].field[aModBonus].value + herofield[tHitDice].value/2
DC = round(DC, 0, -1)

var dam as number
dam = 3 + hero.child[aCHA].field[aModBonus].value
dam = maximum(dam, 1)

   field[xSumm].text = "Cleric is favored class. 1/day, gaze for " & dam & " cold dam & fatigue (DC" & DC & " Fort neg)."]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fColdEndur" name="Cold Endurance" description="Either because of growing up in a frostfell or training your body and mind to ignore the biting effect of cold, you can exist with ease in low-temperature environments.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Base Fortitude save bonus +2.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You can exist comfortably in conditions between 0&#176; F and 90&#176; F without having to make Fortitude saves (as described in Cold Dangers, page 8). You also gain a +2 bonus on saving throws against cold effects.\n\nCold Endurance doesn&#146;t provide any level of resistance to cold damage.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="+2 bon to saves vs cold effects, no need to save at 0&#176;-90&#176; F." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Base Fortitude save +2 required."><![CDATA[child[vFort].field[vBase].value >= 2]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fColdFocus" name="Cold Focus" description="Your cold spells are more potent than normal.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Add +1 to the DC for all saving throws against spells you cast with the cold descriptor. This bonus stacks with similar bonuses, such as those granted by Spell Focus and Greater Spell Focus.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="Cold spells gain +1 DC. Stacks with spell focus." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fColdSpSpe" name="Cold Spell Specialization" description="You do additional damage with cold spells.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Con 13, Snowcasting, Frozen Magic.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: In cold areas (temperature at or below 40&#176; F), you gain a +1 bonus per die to any dice rolled to determine damage caused by cold spells you cast. For example, if an 11th-level wizard with this feat casts a {i}cone of cold{/i} in a cold area, the spell does 11d6+11 points of damage.\n\nIn areas of extreme cold (below &#150;20&#176; F), the damage bonus increases to +2 per die.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="If temp below 40&#176; F gain +1 bon dam per die for cold spells, +2 below &#150;20&#176; F." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Snowcasting required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fSnowcast] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Frozen Magic required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fFrozenMag] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Constitution 13 required."><![CDATA[child[aCON].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fCrafSkTal" name="Craft Skull Talisman" description="You can create skull talismans, which carry spells within themselves (for more information on skull talismans, see page 112).\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Caster level 6th.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You can create a skull talisman of any spell you know and that targets one or more creatures. Crafting a skull talisman takes one day. When you create a skull talisman, you set the caster level. The caster level must be sufficient to cast the spell in question and no higher than your own level. The base price of a skull talisman is its spell level &#215; its caster level &#215; 100 gp. To craft the talisman, you must spend 1/25 of this base price in XP and use up raw materials (mostly comprised of the rare metallic inks needed to inscribe the runes of power on the skull) costing one-half this base price.\n\nWhen you create a skull talisman, you make any choices that you would normally make when casting the spell. Whoever destroys the skull is the target of the spell.\n\nAny skull talisman that stores a spell with a costly material component or a XP cost also carries a commensurate cost. In addition to the costs derived from the base price, you must expend the material component or pay the XP when creating the skull talisman.\n\nThe skull to be used to create a skull talisman must be from a creature of at least Small size. A Small creature&#146;s skull can store a spell of up to 3rd level. A Medium creature&#146;s skull can store a spell of up to 6th level. A Large creature&#146;s skull can store a spell of up to 9th level. The art of crafting skull talismans was perfected by neanderthal druids, but any spellcaster can learn the art of making these devices. Many view the act of creating or using a skull talisman as a distasteful activity, but neither in and of itself is an evil act.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="Inscribe spells onto a skull, discharged when broken." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="ItemCreate"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Caster level 6th required."><![CDATA[tagcount[Hero.Caster] >= 6]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fFaithFros" name="Faith in the Frost" description="You channel frozen energies from your deity when you turn or rebuke creatures.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Ability to turn or rebuke creatures, access to Cold or Winter cleric domain.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: When you successfully turn or rebuke a creature, it takes cold damage equal to your Charisma modifier as blasts of ice and cold energy tear through its body.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="When you turn/rebuke a creature, it takes X cold dam." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostAt" priority="10000"><![CDATA[var dam as number
dam = hero.child[aCHA].field[aModBonus].value
dam = maximum(dam, 0)

   field[xSumm].text = "When you turn/rebuke a creature, it takes " & dam & " cold dam."]]></eval>
    <exprreq message="Turn Undead required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Hero.TurnUndead] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fFroFelPro" name="Frostfell Prodigy" description="You gain additional bonus spells in cold regions.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Con 13, Snowcasting, Frozen Magic, Cold Focus.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: In cold areas (temperature at or below 40&#176; F), the ability score used to determine how many bonus spells you may prepare or cast is treated as if it were 2 higher than its actual score. If you enter an area with a warmer temperature and remain in this area for longer than 1 minute, the bonus spells granted by this feat are lost until you can regain them.\n\nIn areas of extreme cold (below &#150;20&#176; F), the ability score is treated as if it were 4 higher than its actual score for purposes of determining how many bonus spells you can prepare or cast.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="Below 40&#176; F ability score to grant bon spl is 2 higher, below &#150;20&#176; F is 4 higher." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Snowcasting required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fSnowcast] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Frozen Magic required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fFrozenMag] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Cold Focus required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fColdFocus] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Constitution 13 required."><![CDATA[child[aCON].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fFrozenBer" name="Frozen Berserker" description="When you enter your barbarian rage, your body becomes infused with cold energy.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Ability to rage.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: As long as you are under the effects of a barbarian rage, you gain the cold subtype. You gain immunity to cold, but have vulnerability to fire, which means you take half again as much (+50%) damage as normal from fire, regardless of whether a saving throw is allowed, or if the save is a success or failure.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="While raging you have the cold subtype (Imm to cold, vuln to fire)." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Rage or frenzy required."><![CDATA[hero.childfound[cAveRage].tagis[Helper.ShowSpec] + hero.childfound[cBbnRage].tagis[Helper.ShowSpec] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fFrozenMag" name="Frozen Magic" description="Your cold spells are more powerful when you cast them in a cold region.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Con 13, Snowcasting.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: In cold areas (temperature at or below 40&#176; F), spells with the cold descriptor cast by you manifest at caster level +1.\n\nIn areas of extreme cold (below &#150;20&#176; F), cold spells cast by you manifest at caster level +2.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="Below 40&#176; F cold spells are +1 CL, below &#150;20&#176; F are +2 CL." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Snowcasting required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fSnowcast] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Constitution 13 required."><![CDATA[child[aCON].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fFroWildSh" name="Frozen Wild Shape" description="You can assume the form of magical beasts with the cold subtype.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Base Fortitude save bonus +6, wild shape ability.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You may use your wild shape ability to assume the form of any magical beast with the cold subtype. Your new form must still fall within the size limitations of your wild shape ability. As with the standard wild shape ability, you do not gain any of the extraordinary special qualities or any supernatural abilities possessed by the new form, with the exception of the cold subtype. This subtype grants you immunity to cold but vulnerability to fire, which means you take half again as much (+50%) damage as normal from fire while in a frozen wild shape, regardless of whether a saving throw is allowed, or if the save is a success or failure.\n\nPossible cold magical beasts from the Monster Manual include cryohydras (Huge wild shape required), frost worms (Huge wild shape required), and winter wolves.\n\nPossible cold magical beasts from Monster Manual II include frost salamanders.\n\nPossible cold magical beasts from this book include brantas (Large wild shape required), ice toads (Large wild shape required), urskans (Large wild shape required), and tlalusks (Huge wild shape required).\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="May Wild Shape into cold magical beasts." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Wild Shape required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Hero.WildShape] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base Fortitude save +6 required."><![CDATA[child[vFort].field[vBase].value >= 6]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fColdFocGr" name="Greater Cold Focus" description="Your cold spells are now even more potent than before.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Cold Focus.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Add +1 to the DC for all saving throws against spells with the cold descriptor. This bonus stacks with similar bonuses, such as those from Cold Focus, Spell Focus, and Greater Spell Focus.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="Cold spells gain +1 DC. Stacks with spell focus &amp; cold focus." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Cold Focus required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fColdFocus] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fIcyCallin" name="Icy Calling" description="Your summon spells work better in the frostfell if you summon native creatures.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Con 13, Snowcasting.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: In cold areas (temperature at or below 40&#176; F), creatures native to cold environments and creatures with the cold subtype summoned by you are more powerful and agile than normal. The summoned creatures gain a +4 enhancement bonus to Strength and Dexterity for the duration of the spell that summoned them.\n\nIn areas of extreme cold (below &#150;20&#176; F), any summoned creature affected by this feat has maximum hit points when summoned.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="Below 40&#176; F summon cold ally gain +4 Str &amp; Dex enh bon, below &#150;20&#176; F max Hp." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Snowcasting required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fSnowcast] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Constitution 13 required."><![CDATA[child[aCON].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fIceHarmon" name="Ice Harmonics" description="You can use your voice to shatter ice.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Bardic music ability, Perform (sing) 6 ranks.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: By expending one of your daily uses of bardic music, you can cause any unattended non magical ice object or portion of ice to explode violently. The target must be within 30 feet, and you must be able to sing in order to shatter the ice. Any creature located in the 5-foot square in which you target with this ability takes piercing damage equal to 2d6 + your Charisma modifier. Creatures made of ice that you specifically target with this effect take double damage.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="Use 1 music ice in 30 ft explodes for 2d6+X pierce dam, dbl vs ice creature." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostAt" priority="10000"><![CDATA[var dam as number
dam = hero.child[aCHA].field[aModBonus].value

if (dam > 0) then
   field[xSumm].text = "Use 1 music, ice in 30 ft explodes for 2d6+" & dam & " pierce dam, dbl vs ice creature."
elseif (dam = 0) then
   field[xSumm].text = "Use 1 music, ice in 30 ft explodes for 2d6 pierce dam, dbl vs ice creature."
elseif (dam < 0) then
   field[xSumm].text = "Use 1 music, ice in 30 ft explodes for 2d6-" & dam & " pierce dam, dbl vs ice creature."
endif]]></eval>
    <exprreq message="Perform (Sing) 6 ranks required."><![CDATA[#skillranks[kPerfSing] >= 6]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Bardic Music required."><![CDATA[picklives[hBrdMusic] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fImpColEnd" name="Improved Cold Endurance" description="Your training and natural hardiness have improved your natural resistance to cold temperatures.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Base Fortitude save bonus +6, Cold Endurance.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You gain resistance to cold 5. If you already have resistance to cold, it increases by 5 (maximum resistance to cold 15).\n\n{b}Special{/b}: You can gain this feat multiple times; its effects stack. You cannot have more than resistance to cold 15 as a result of taking this feat.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xImpColEnd"></bootstrap>
    <exprreq message="Base Fortitude save +6 required."><![CDATA[child[vFort].field[vBase].value >= 6]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Cold Endurance required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fColdEndur] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fImpFrosTo" name="Improved Frosty Touch" description="Your frosty touch causes more cold damage.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Uldra.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Your frosty touch ability now deals 2 points of cold damage.\n\n{b}Normal{/b}: Your frosty touch ability deals 1 point of cold damage.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="Frosty touch deals 2 points of cold dam." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Uldra race required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Uldra] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fMarkHleid" name="Mark of Hleid" description="You bear a birthmark in the shape of the holy symbol of Hleid (a ragged white triangle with a vortex of blue flame in its center) somewhere on your body; this mark identifies you as an ally of the church of Hleid and grants you supernatural qualities.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Your patron deity must be Hleid.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: The actual birthmark itself radiates faint abjuration magic if it is viewed with a {i}detect magic{/i} spell, and faint good if viewed with a {i}detect good{/i} spell.\n\nYou are immune to the frost touch special attack of a rimefire eidolon. Additionally, you can handle rimefire ice barehanded without taking any cold damage.\n\nCleric is now a favored class for you; the cleric class does not count when determining whether you take an experience point penalty for multiclassing.\n\nYou gain a +2 sacred bonus to your Armor Class against evil-aligned creatures with the cold subtype.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: If you ever lose favor with Hleid, or change your patron deity to another deity, the mark of Hleid fades and you lose all benefits of this feat. You do not gain a replacement feat. If you later return to Hleid&#146;s faithful and receive an {i}atonement{/i} spell, the mark reappears and you regain the benefits of the feat.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="Imm to rimefire ice &amp; eidolon frost touch, +2 sac bon to AC vs evil cold foes." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fMountaine" name="Mountaineer" description="You are a particularly gifted explorer and mountain climber.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You get a +2 bonus on all Climb and Survival checks.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Eval (Done)</comment>
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <eval phase="PreLevel" priority="5000"><![CDATA[
      ~ If we're disabled, do nothing
      if (tagis[Helper.FtDisable] <> 0) then
        done
        endif

      #skillbonus[kClimb] += 2
      #skillbonus[kSurvival] += 2]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fPiercCold" name="Piercing Cold" description="Your cold spells are so cold that they can damage creatures normally resistant or immune to cold.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You can only apply this metamagic feat to spells with the cold descriptor. Piercing cold spells are so horribly cold that they are capable of damaging creatures normally unharmed by or resistant to cold. Piercing cold spells completely ignore any resistance to cold a creature possesses, bypassing this resistance and dealing damage to the target as if it did not possess any resistance to cold at all. They are still entitled to whatever other defenses the attack allows (such as saving throws and spell resistance).\n\nCreatures normally immune to cold can be damaged by piercing cold spells as well. Piercing cold spells deal half damage to these creatures (or one-quarter on a successful saving throw).\n\nFor example, Mialee casts a piercing cold {i}cone of cold{/i} at a night hag, a creature normally immune to cold. She makes her level check to penetrate the night hag&#146;s spell resistance, but the night hag makes her Reflex save against the spell. Mialee rolls the dice, and her {i}cone of cold{/i} deals 42 points of cold damage; since the night hag made her save, the damage is halved to 21 points. This damage is then halved again (since the night hag is normally immune to cold), and 10 points of cold damage are actually dealt to the night hag, who is both shocked and enraged at this unexpected turn of events.\n\nCreatures with the cold subtype can tell that a piercing cold spell is colder than normal, but they remain undamaged by the attack.\n\nCreatures with the fire subtype who are damaged by a piercing cold spell take double normal damage instead of the usual +50%.\n\nA piercing cold spell uses up a spell slot one level higher than the spell&#146;s actual level.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="Cold spell ignore cold resist, 1/2 dam vs imm, dbl dam vs fire. +1 Level." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Metamagic"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fPrimevWS" name="Primeval Wild Shape" description="Your wild shape forms are stronger than normal.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Wild shape ability.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: When you assume a wild shape form, you can opt to cause the shape assumed to be a primeval form of the creature that existed in the ancient past during a vast ice age. Doing so grants the new form a +2 racial bonus to Strength, a +2 bonus to its natural armor, and resistance to cold 10. A primeval wild shape has a much shorter duration than normal, since the enhanced qualities of the new shape drain your supernatural energies much more quickly. A primeval wild shape has a duration of 1 round per druid level (or per level of the class that granted you the wild shape ability) instead of the normal 1 hour per druid level.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="Wild shape form has +2 Str, nat armor &amp; cold resist 10, duration is 1 rd per lvl." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Wild Shape required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Hero.WildShape] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fPrimCast" name="Primitive Caster" description="You use screeches, wild gesticulations, and extra material components to give your spells additional power.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: This feat only functions when you cast a spell that does not already have a verbal, somatic, or material component. For each component you voluntarily add, you increase the effective caster level of the spell by +1. You can only add a component that&#146;s not already present in the spell. For example, you can&#146;t add a somatic component to a {i}gaseous form{/i} spell, because it already has one. You could add a verbal component, however.\n\nThe verbal component you add consists of animalistic shouts, screams, and growls. The DC of Listen checks to hear you cast a spell is &#150;5 (before modifying for distance). The somatic component is also more complex, so you must have two hands free to add a somatic component with this feat. The extra material component you add with this feat must be a rare plant found in the frostfell, which requires a successful DC 15 Profession (herbalist) check to locate.\n\nThis feat originally appeared in Races of Faer&#251;n.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="Add verbal, somatic, material comp to spell without one for +1 CL each." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSeaLeg" name="Sea Legs" description="You are accustomed to the rolling motion on board a ship, and can use this motion to your advantage.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: As long as you are on board a ship, you get a +2 bonus on all Balance and Tumble checks, and a +1 bonus on Initiative checks.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="On ship gain +2 bon to Balance &amp; Tumble, +1 bon to Initiative." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSmitFirFo" name="Smite Fiery Foe" description="You can smite creatures with the fire subtype.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Smite ability.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Once per day, you may attempt to smite a creature with the fire subtype with a normal melee attack. When you activate this ability, your attack becomes infused with cold energy. You add your Charisma modifier to your attack roll and deal 1 extra point of cold damage per character level. If you smite a creature that does not have the fire subtype, the blast of cold does not manifest and the smite attempt is used up for that day.\n\nRemember that creatures with the fire subtype take half again as much (+50%) damage as normal from cold, including the additional damage dealt by this ability.\n\nYou may swap out any daily uses of a smite ability gained by a character class or cleric domain to smite fiery foes instead.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="1/day, smite fire foes, +X bon to hit, +YY cold dam. Regain with other smites." uniqueness="useronce">
    <fieldval field="hTotal" value="1"/>
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostAt" priority="10000"><![CDATA[
   field[xSumm].text = "1/day, smite fire foes, +" & hero.child[aCHA].field[aModBonus].value & " bon to hit, +" & herofield[tHitDice].value & " cold dam. Regain with other smites."]]></eval>
    <prereq message="Smite ability required.">
      <validate><![CDATA[    @valid = 0
  if (pickexists[cPalSmite1] + pickexists[xFieSmite] + pickexists[xCelSmite] + pickexists[cPfChvSmit] + pickexists[cBlkSmite1] + pickexists[cBlkPalSm1] + pickexists[cdDestSmit] <> 0) then
    @valid = 1
  endif]]></validate>
      </prereq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSnowcast" name="Snowcasting" description="You add ice or snow to your spell&#146;s components to make them more powerful.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Con 13.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: If you add a handful of snow or ice as an additional material component to a spell when you cast it, the spell gains the cold descriptor. This does not actually change the nature of the spell you cast; a {i}fireball{/i} cast with this feat still deals fire damage, but since it also carries the cold descriptor, it can be augmented by a number of feats listed in this chapter, such as Cold Focus and Frozen Magic.\n\nIf you add a handful of snow or ice as an additional material component to a spell when you cast it and that spell already has the cold descriptor, you increase the effective level of the spell being cast by +1.\n\nAdding this additional material component requires you to spend a move action immediately before the spell is cast to gather fresh snow or ice from the surrounding environment. This snow or ice can be magically created by a conjuration spell, but no other ice manifested by a spell will do. You may take no other action between gathering the snow or ice and casting the spell.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="Move, use snow as M comp to add cold desc to spell cast that rd or +1 CL if has." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Constitution 13 required."><![CDATA[child[aCON].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSnowrun" name="Snowrunner" description="You are particularly adept at moving through snow and over ice.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Woodland stride ability.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You can move through loose snow at full speed, as if you were moving across open terrain. You are also skilled at moving across open ice, and gain a +5 competence bonus on Balance checks to avoid slipping when you move across icy surfaces.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="Loose snow does not slow you, +5 to Balance to avoid slip on ice." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="User" tag="WoodStride" name="Woodland Stride"/>
    <exprreq message="Woodland Stride required."><![CDATA[hero.childfound[cDrdWoodS].tagis[Helper.ShowSpec] + hero.childfound[cRgrWoodS].tagis[Helper.ShowSpec] + hero.tagis[User.WoodStride] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSnowFWarD" name="Snowflake Wardance" description="You have mastered the snowflake wardance, a mystical style of fighting with slashing weapons that allows you to leap and almost seem to float haphazardly across the battlefield like a whirling, razor-edged snowflake.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Bardic music ability, Perform (dance) 6 ranks.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: By expending one of your daily uses of bardic music, you may perform a deadly style of combat known as the snowflake wardance. Activating a snowflake wardance is a free action, and once activated, you add your Charisma modifier to your attack rolls with any slashing melee weapon you wield in one hand. This bonus to hit stacks with any bonuses you get from a high Strength score (or Dexterity score, if you are using Weapon Finesse).\n\nYou cannot use this feat if you are carrying a shield, wearing medium or heavy armor, or carrying a medium or heavy load.\n\nA snowflake wardance lasts for a number of rounds equal to your ranks in Perform (dance). Performing a snowflake wardance is physically tiresome&#151;when the snowflake wardance ends, you become fatigued for the next 10 minutes.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="Free, use 1 music, in light/no armor &amp; no shl gain +X bon to att with slash wep." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostAt" priority="10000"><![CDATA[var dam as number
dam = hero.child[aCHA].field[aModBonus].value

  field[xSumm].text = "Free, use 1 music, in light/no armor & no shl gain +" & dam & " bon to att with slash wep."]]></eval>
    <exprreq message="Perform (Dance) 6 ranks required."><![CDATA[#skillranks[kPerfDance] >= 6]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Bardic Music required."><![CDATA[picklives[hBrdMusic] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fStormMagi" name="Storm Magic" description="You gain a boost in spellcasting power during storms.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: All spells you cast while you are affected by a storm (either natural or magical) manifest at +1 caster level. For more information on storms, see page 94 of the Dungeon Master&#146;s Guide.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="All spells cast during storm gain +1 CL." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSugMaster" name="Sugliin Mastery" description="You are a master at fighting with the massive sugliin.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Base attack bonus +5, Exotic Weapon Proficiency (sugliin).\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You can attack with a sugliin as if it were a normal weapon, either making a single attack as a standard action or a full attack as a full-round action.\n\n{b}Normal{/b}: Making a single attack with a sugliin is always a full-round action.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="You can attack with the sugliin as though it were a normal weapon." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Exotic Weapon Proficiency (Sugliin) required."><![CDATA[tagis[WepProf.wSugliin] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base attack bonus +5 required."><![CDATA[child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 5]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fWinChamp" name="Winter&apos;s Champion" description="Your paladin spell list is enhanced.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Paladin level 1st.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: When you gain this feat, you may add the 1st-, 2nd-, 3rd-, and 4th-level spells granted by the Cold and Winter domains as paladin spells of the same levels. You do not gain the ability to cast spells of these domains of 5th level or higher, nor do you gain the granted powers of the domains.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: If you have any levels of cleric, these additional domains are not available to your cleric levels, since they are technically paladin spells in this case.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="Add 1st-4th domain spells of Cold &amp; Winter to paladin spell list." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Paladin level 1st required."><![CDATA[#levelcount[Paladin] >= 1]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fWinMount" name="Winter&apos;s Mount" description="Your special mount is native to the frostfell.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Special mount ability.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Your special mount gains the cold subtype. It gains immunity to cold, but has vulnerability to fire, which means it takes half again as much (+50%) damage as normal from fire, regardless of whether a saving throw is allowed, or if the save is a success or failure.\n\nYour special mount is also hardier than a non frostfell version; it gains a +2 racial bonus to Constitution.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Feat" summary="Special mount gains cold subtype and +2 Constitution." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Special Mount required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[CompAvail.cPalMount] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="xImpColEnd" name="Improved Cold Endurance" description="You have the specified Damage Resistance against Cold attacks." compset="Special" uniqueness="unique">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="Feat" name="Feat" abbrev="Feat"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xDamRsCold"></bootstrap>
    <eval phase="Final" priority="10100" index="2"><![CDATA[    ~ if we have no cold resistance, apply our ShowSpec tag and rename ourselves to Cold Resistance X. Else rename the fire resistance thing to current value +X.
    var feats as number
    feats = minimum(hero.tagcount[HasFeat.fImpColEnd], 3)
    feats = feats * 5

    if (hero.child[xDamRsCold].field[Value].value = 0) then
      perform assign[Helper.ShowSpec]
      field[livename].text = "Damage Resistance, Cold (" & feats & ")"
    else
      var nat as number
      nat = hero.child[xDamRsCold].field[Value].value

      var total as number
      total = feats + nat

      hero.child[xDamRsCold].field[livename].text = "Damage Resistance, Cold (" & total & ")"      
    endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="mmPiercCol" name="Piercing Cold" description="Your cold spells are so cold that they can damage creatures normally resistant or immune to cold.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You can only apply this metamagic feat to spells with the cold descriptor. Piercing cold spells are so horribly cold that they are capable of damaging creatures normally unharmed by or resistant to cold. Piercing cold spells completely ignore any resistance to cold a creature possesses, bypassing this resistance and dealing damage to the target as if it did not possess any resistance to cold at all. They are still entitled to whatever other defenses the attack allows (such as saving throws and spell resistance).\n\nCreatures normally immune to cold can be damaged by piercing cold spells as well. Piercing cold spells deal half damage to these creatures (or one-quarter on a successful saving throw).\n\nFor example, Mialee casts a piercing cold {i}cone of cold{/i} at a night hag, a creature normally immune to cold. She makes her level check to penetrate the night hag&#146;s spell resistance, but the night hag makes her Reflex save against the spell. Mialee rolls the dice, and her {i}cone of cold{/i} deals 42 points of cold damage; since the night hag made her save, the damage is halved to 21 points. This damage is then halved again (since the night hag is normally immune to cold), and 10 points of cold damage are actually dealt to the night hag, who is both shocked and enraged at this unexpected turn of events.\n\nCreatures with the cold subtype can tell that a piercing cold spell is colder than normal, but they remain undamaged by the attack.\n\nCreatures with the fire subtype who are damaged by a piercing cold spell take double normal damage instead of the usual +50%.\n\nA piercing cold spell uses up a spell slot one level higher than the spell&#146;s actual level." compset="Metamagic" summary="Cold spell ignores resistance, does half dam to Immune." uniqueness="unique">
    <comment>@valid = hero.pickexists[fSilentSpl] + parent.tagis[Helper.OnScroll]</comment>
    <fieldval field="mmAbbr" value="Cold"/>
    <fieldval field="mmLevel" value="1"/>
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <prereq message="Piercing Cold required.">
      <validate>@valid = hero.pickexists[fPiercCold] + parent.tagis[Helper.OnScroll]</validate>
      </prereq>
    </thing>
