  <thing id="xFMaGaiKno" name="Gain Knowledge" description="Beginning at 3rd level, the frost mage gains knowledge of the spell {i}conjure ice beast I{/i}, if he does not already have it. Former wizards get to add this spell to their spellbooks for free, and former sorcerers and bards get to add this spell to their spells known, even if this takes them over their normal limit. For each two levels gained in the prestige class, he gains knowledge of the next higher level in the {i}conjure ice beast{/i} spell progression ({i}conjure ice beast II{/i} at 5th level, {i}conjure ice beast III{/i} at 7th level, and {i}conjure ice beast IV{/i} at 9th level). At 7th level, in addition to gaining {i}conjure ice beast III{/i}, the frost mage gains {i}animate snow{/i} as a spell known. At 9th level, in addition to gaining {i}conjure ice beast IV{/i}, the frost mage gains {i}frostfell{/i} as a spell known.\n\nThis class feature does not change the level of the spell. A frost mage still must have a spell slot of the appropriate level to prepare or cast a spell acquired through the gain knowledge ability." compset="Special" summary="Add XXX to spellbook/spells known." uniqueness="unique">
    <usesource source="Frostburn"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpFMa"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
