  <thing id="sWizBorWin" name="Boreal Wind" description="You create a strong blast of arctic air {b}20 ft. wide, 20 ft. high{/b} that originates from your fingertips and moves in the direction you are facing {b} out to the extreme of the range{/b}. As a stronger form of {i}gust of wind{/i}, this boreal wind automatically extinguishes candles, torches, and similar protected or unprotected flames, including lanterns. Large fires (such as bonfires, a blacksmith&#146;s coals, or even a house fire) have a 50% chance to be extinguished by the {i}boreal wind{/i}. Forest or grassland fires are too large to be extinguished by this spell.\n\nAll creatures caught in the area take 1d4 points of cold damage per caster level (maximum 15d4). A successful Fortitude saving throw negates the gust&#146;s effects. Those that fail the save are pushed away from the caster a distance of 3 feet per caster level. Creatures that remain in the area past the first round must make an additional saving throw each round.\n\nA {i}boreal wind{/i} can do anything a sudden blast of wind would be expected to do. It can create a stinging spray of sand or dust, overturn tents and blow down small huts, scuttle a small boat, and blow gases or vapors to the edge of the range.\n\nThe wind can change direction if you actively direct it (a move action for you); otherwise, it merely blows in the same direction." compset="Spell" summary="Gust of cold wind deals 1d4 cold damage/level and knocks creatures back.">
