  <thing id="sSorIcebur" name="Iceburg" description="{i}Iceberg{/i} is a brutal and direct spell. When cast, the spell creates a single large block of ice that drops from the sky onto a spot you select. The iceberg then shatters if it encounters a solid surface. Elephant-sized blocks of ice scatter in all directions, affecting creatures {b}in a 60-foot radius{/b} based on how far they are from the center of the area.\n\n{i}Within 20 Feet of the Center Point{/i}: Any creature or object directly beneath the iceberg takes 20d6 points of crushing damage (no save) and is buried in snow (see page 90).\n\n{i}Between 20 Feet and 40 Feet of the Center Point{/i}: Creatures and objects in the middle section of the area also take 20d6 points of crushing damage, but are entitled to a Reflex save for half damage. They are buried in snow (see page 90).\n\n{i}Between 40 Feet and 60 Feet of the Center Point{/i}: Creatures in the outermost section may be struck by flying debris for 10d6 points of damage. They are entitled to a Reflex save for half damage, and are not buried regardless of whether the saving throw is successful or not." compset="Spell" summary="Block of ice falls from sky, dealing 20d6 damage and burying subjects.">
