  <thing id="sClrPasIce" name="Pass through Ice" description="The transmuted creature is able to pass through ice or snow as easily as water, but not through stone or frozen mud. The creature moves at a speed of 15 feet and can rise or sink into ice at a rate of 5 feet per round.\n\nWhen a {i}pass through ice{/i} spell ends, the affected creature is ejected out to the nearest ice surface. If someone dispels {i}pass through ice{/i} or you dismiss it while a creature is still in the ice, the creatures may be trapped in the ice unless they can reach the nearest surface within a single round of movement. Creatures trapped act as if caught in an {i}entomb{/i} spell." compset="Spell" summary="Subject can pass through ice or snow like water.">
