  <thing id="sDrdSnowdr" name="Snowdrift" description="You can form existing snow {b}(up to 10 cu. ft. +1 cu. ft./level){/b} into any shape that suits your purpose. For example, you can make a snowbank for concealment, sculpt a snow statue or idol, open a tunnel in deep snow, or simply cover a set of tracks. {i}Snowdrift{/i} also permits you to raise snowy barriers around a door or house to prevent vision in or out, or to clog a chimney with snow. Snow cannot be made into weapons with this spell, and {i}snowdrift{/i} does not affect solid ice in any form.\n\n{i}Arcane Material Component{/i}: A pinch of white flour." compset="Spell" summary="Forms existing snow into another shape.">
