  <thing id="sSpTGlGlIn" name="Glacial Globe of Invulnerability" description="A frosty sphere of cold energy surrounds you {b}(a 10-ft.-radius spherical emanation){/b} and excludes all spells and spell-like abilities with the fire descriptor of 3rd level or lower. This spell functions like {i}globe of invulnerability{/i}, except that it affects only fire spells. In addition, the frosty opaqueness of the globe grants concealment (20% miss chance) to those within the area against attacks from outside. Likewise, targets outside the globe gain concealment against attacks from those within the spell&#146;s area.\n\n{i}Arcane Material Component{/i}: A tiny sphere of ice that shatters at the expiration of the spell." compset="Spell" summary="Stops 1stthrough 3rd-level fire spell effects and provides concealment.">
