  <thing id="wRitiik" name="Ritiik" description="A ritiik is a spearlike weapon with an additional hooklike blade protruding from the base of the spear head. When you successfully hit a target with a ritiik, you can twist the weapon and hook this blade into the target&#146;s flesh if the target fails a Reflex saving throw (DC 10 + the damage dealt). If you hook the target, you can immediately make a trip attack against the target. If you fail, you can let go of the ritiik to avoid the retaliatory trip attack.\n\nThe damaged creature can pull the ritiik from its wound if it has two free hands and takes a full-round action to do so, but it deals damage to itself equal to the initial damage the ritiik dealt. A character who succeeds on a DC 15 Heal check can remove a ritiik without further damage.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Frostburn" compset="Weapon">
    <fieldval field="gSizeCost" value="5"/>
